Path: godot/classes/class_systemfont.rst
Summary: Describes the SystemFont class, which loads fonts from the operating system and inherits from Font, Resource, RefCounted, and Object.
SystemFont
Inherits: Font < Resource < RefCounted < Object

A font loaded from a system font. Falls back to a default theme font if not implemented on the host OS.
---CHUNK---
Document: SystemFont
Path: godot/classes/class_systemfont.rst
Summary: Loads a font from the system using a list of preferred font names and styles.
Inherits: Font < Resource < RefCounted < Object
Description: SystemFont loads a font from a system font with the first matching name from font_names. It will attempt to match font style, but it's not guaranteed. The returned font might be part of a font collection or be a variable font with OpenType "weight", "width" and/or "italic" features set. You can create FontVariation of the system font for precise control over its features. Note: This class is implemented on iOS, Linux, macOS and Windows, on other platforms it will fallback to default theme font.
---CHUNK---
Document: SystemFont
Path: godot/classes/class_systemfont.rst
Summary: Defines the properties available for the SystemFont class in Godot Engine.

Properties
- allow_system_fallback (bool): If true, allows the font to fall back to a system font if the specified font is not found. Default: true.
- antialiasing (FontAntialiasing): Controls the antialiasing mode for the font. Default: 1.
- disable_embedded_bitmaps (bool): If true, disables the use of embedded bitmaps within the font file. Default: true.
- font_italic (bool): If true, uses the italic variant of the font if available. Default: false.
- font_names (PackedStringArray): An array of font names to try loading. The first available font in the list will be used. Default: PackedStringArray().
- font_stretch (int): Controls the horizontal stretching of the font. Default: 100.
- font_weight (int): Controls the weight (boldness) of the font. Default: 400.
- force_autohinter (bool): If true, forces the use of an autohinter for font rendering. Default: false.
- generate_mipmaps (bool): If true, generates mipmaps for the font texture. Default: false.
- hinting (Hinting): Controls the hinting mode for font rendering. Default: 1.
- keep_rounding_remainders (bool): If true, preserves rounding remainders for potentially more accurate glyph positioning. Default: true.
- modulate_color_glyphs (bool): If true, allows color glyphs to be modulated by the font's color. Default: false.
- msdf_pixel_range (int): The pixel range used for Multi-channel Signed Distance Field (MSDF) rendering. Default: 16.
- msdf_size (int): The size of the MSDF texture atlas. Default: 48.
- multichannel_signed_distance_field (bool): If true, enables multichannel signed distance field rendering for the font. Default: false.
- oversampling (float): Controls the oversampling factor for font rendering, improving sharpness at the cost of performance. Default: 0.0.
- subpixel_positioning (SubpixelPositioning): Controls the subpixel positioning mode for font rendering. Default: 1.
---CHUNK---
Document: SystemFont
Path: godot/classes/class_systemfont.rst
Summary: Describes the properties and member variables of the SystemFont class in Godot Engine.

Property: allow_system_fallback
Type: bool
Description: If set to true, system fonts can be automatically used as fallbacks.
Default: true
Method: set_allow_system_fallback(value: bool)
Method: is_allow_system_fallback() -> bool

Property: antialiasing
Type: FontAntialiasing
Description: Font anti-aliasing mode.
Default: 1
Method: set_antialiasing(value: FontAntialiasing)
Method: get_antialiasing() -> FontAntialiasing

Property: disable_embedded_bitmaps
Type: bool
Description: If set to true, embedded font bitmap loading is disabled (bitmap-only and color fonts ignore this property).
Default: true
Method: set_disable_embedded_bitmaps(value: bool)
Method: get_disable_embedded_bitmaps() -> bool

Property: font_italic
Type: bool
Description: If set to true, italic or oblique font is preferred.
Default: false
Method: set_font_italic(value: bool)
Method: get_font_italic() -> bool

Property: font_names
Type: PackedStringArray
Description: Array of font family names to search, first matching font found is used.
Default: PackedStringArray()
Method: set_font_names(value: PackedStringArray)
Method: get_font_names() -> PackedStringArray
Note: The returned array is copied and any changes to it will not update the original property value.

Property: font_stretch
Type: int
Description: Preferred font stretch amount, compared to a normal width. A percentage value between 50% and 200%.
Default: 100
Method: set_font_stretch(value: int)
Method: get_font_stretch() -> int

Property: font_weight
Type: int
Description: Preferred weight (boldness) of the font. A value in the 100...999 range, normal font weight is 400, bold font weight is 700.
Default: 400
Method: set_font_weight(value: int)
Method: get_font_weight() -> int

Property: force_autohinter
Type: bool
Description: If set to true, auto-hinting is supported and preferred over font built-in hinting.
Default: false
Method: set_force_autohinter(value: bool)
Method: is_force_autohinter() -> bool

Property: generate_mipmaps
Type: bool
Description: If set to true, generate mipmaps for the font textures.
Default: false
Method: set_generate_mipmaps(value: bool)
Method: get_generate_mipmaps() -> bool

Property: hinting
Type: Hinting
Description: Font hinting mode.
Default: 1
Method: set_hinting(value: Hinting)
Method: get_hinting() -> Hinting

Property: keep_rounding_remainders
Type: bool
Description: If set to true, when aligning glyphs to the pixel boundaries rounding remainders are accumulated to ensure more uniform glyph distribution. This setting has no effect if subpixel positioning is enabled.
Default: true
Method: set_keep_rounding_remainders(value: bool)
Method: get_keep_rounding_remainders() -> bool

Property: modulate_color_glyphs
Type: bool
Description: If set to true, color modulation is applied when drawing colored glyphs, otherwise it's applied to the monochrome glyphs only.
Default: false
Method: set_modulate_color_glyphs(value: bool)
Method: is_modulate_color_glyphs() -> bool

Property: msdf_pixel_range
Type: int
Description: The width of the range around the shape between the minimum and maximum representable signed distance. If using font outlines, msdf_pixel_range must be set to at least twice the size of the largest font outline. The default msdf_pixel_range value of 16 allows outline sizes up to 8 to look correct.
Default: 16
Method: set_msdf_pixel_range(value: int)
Method: get_msdf_pixel_range() -> int

Property: msdf_size
Type: int
Description: Source font size used to generate MSDF textures. Higher values allow for more precision, but are slower to render and require more memory. Only increase this value if you notice a visible lack of precision in glyph rendering.
Default: 48
Method: set_msdf_size(value: int)
Method: get_msdf_size() -> int

Property: multichannel_signed_distance_field
Type: bool
Description: If set to true, glyphs of all sizes are rendered using single multichannel signed distance field generated from the dynamic font vector data.
Default: false
Method: set_multichannel_signed_distance_field(value: bool)
Method: is_multichannel_signed_distance_field() -> bool

Property: oversampling
Type: float
Description: If set to a positive value, overrides the oversampling factor of the viewport this font is used in. See Viewport.oversampling. This value doesn't override the oversampling parameter of draw_* methods.
Default: 0.0
Method: set_oversampling(value: float)
Method: get_oversampling() -> float

Property: subpixel_positioning
Type: SubpixelPositioning
Description: Font glyph subpixel positioning mode. Subpixel positioning provides shaper text and better kerning for smaller font sizes, at the cost of memory usage and font rasterization speed. Use TextServer.SUBPIXEL_POSITIONING_AUTO to automatically enable it based on the font size.
Default: 1
Method: set_subpixel_positioning(value: SubpixelPositioning)
Method: get_subpixel_positioning() -> SubpixelPositioning